@startuml
!define RECTANGLE class

title Algorithm Visualization Application - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Browser\n(React App)" as Browser
participant "MyRoute\n(Router)" as Router
participant "MainInterface" as MainInterface
participant "Sidebar" as Sidebar
participant "Map\n(BMap API)" as Map
participant "Panel" as Panel
participant "GraphSVG" as GraphSVG
participant "GraphTable" as GraphTable
participant "eventProxy\n(Pub-Sub)" as EventProxy
participant "Express Server" as ExpressServer
participant "Authorize\n(Middleware)" as Authorize
participant "routes/index.js" as Routes
participant "User Module\n(DAO)" as UserModule
participant "MySQL Database" as Database
participant "C++ Algorithm\n(External Process)" as CppAlgorithm

== Application Initialization ==
User -> Browser: Access Application URL
Browser -> Router: Load Application
Router -> MainInterface: Render Main Interface
MainInterface -> Sidebar: Initialize Sidebar
MainInterface -> Map: Initialize Map with BMap API
MainInterface -> Panel: Initialize Panel
Panel -> GraphSVG: Initialize Graph Visualization
Panel -> GraphTable: Initialize Graph Table
GraphSVG -> EventProxy: Subscribe to events
GraphTable -> EventProxy: Subscribe to events

== User Authentication ==
User -> Sidebar: Enter Credentials
Sidebar -> Browser: Submit Login Form
Browser -> ExpressServer: POST /users/login
ExpressServer -> Authorize: Validate Session
Authorize -> UserModule: Check User Credentials
UserModule -> Database: Query User Data
Database --> UserModule: Return User Record
UserModule --> Authorize: User Validated
Authorize --> ExpressServer: Authentication Success
ExpressServer --> Browser: Session Token
Browser --> User: Login Success

== Algorithm Selection and Node Management ==
User -> Sidebar: Select Algorithm (e.g., DFS, Dijkstra)
Sidebar -> Sidebar: Update UI State
User -> Sidebar: Add/Delete Nodes
Sidebar -> Map: Update Map Markers
Map -> Map: Render/Remove Node Markers
Sidebar -> Panel: Update Graph Data
Panel -> GraphSVG: Refresh Graph Visualization
Panel -> GraphTable: Update Table Data

== Algorithm Execution Request ==
User -> Sidebar: Click "Visualize" Button
Sidebar -> Browser: Prepare Request Data
Browser -> ExpressServer: POST /code (with algorithm params)
ExpressServer -> Authorize: Check Authorization
Authorize -> ExpressServer: Authorized
ExpressServer -> Routes: Handle Algorithm Execution
Routes -> Routes: Write Input to File
Routes -> CppAlgorithm: Spawn External Process (exec)
activate CppAlgorithm
CppAlgorithm -> CppAlgorithm: Execute Algorithm\n(DFS/Dijkstra/etc.)
CppAlgorithm -> CppAlgorithm: Generate Output File
CppAlgorithm --> Routes: Process Complete
deactivate CppAlgorithm
Routes -> Routes: Read Output File
Routes -> Routes: Transform to Animation Steps
Routes -> Database: Persist Algorithm State
Database --> Routes: Save Confirmation
Routes --> ExpressServer: Return Animation Data
ExpressServer --> Browser: JSON Response with Steps
Browser -> Panel: Receive Animation Steps

== Visualization and Animation ==
Panel -> EventProxy: Publish "startAnimation" Event
EventProxy -> GraphSVG: Notify Animation Start
EventProxy -> GraphTable: Notify Animation Start
GraphSVG -> GraphSVG: Begin Step-by-Step Animation
loop For Each Animation Step
    GraphSVG -> Map: Update Node/Edge States
    Map -> Map: Render Visual Changes
    GraphSVG -> EventProxy: Publish "stepUpdate" Event
    EventProxy -> GraphTable: Notify Step Update
    GraphTable -> GraphTable: Highlight Current Row
    GraphSVG -> GraphSVG: Display Code Snippet
    GraphSVG -> GraphSVG: Wait for Animation Delay
end
GraphSVG -> EventProxy: Publish "animationComplete" Event
EventProxy -> GraphTable: Notify Animation Complete
GraphTable -> GraphTable: Reset Highlighting
GraphSVG --> User: Display Completion Status

== View Reports ==
User -> Sidebar: Navigate to Reports
Sidebar -> Router: Route to /reports
Router -> Reports: Render Reports Component
Reports -> Browser: Request Report Data
Browser -> ExpressServer: GET /reports
ExpressServer -> Authorize: Check Authorization
Authorize -> ExpressServer: Authorized
ExpressServer -> Routes: Fetch Report Data
Routes -> Database: Query Algorithm History
Database --> Routes: Return Report Records
Routes --> ExpressServer: Report Data
ExpressServer --> Browser: JSON Response
Browser -> Reports: Display Reports
Reports -> BodyInfo: Render Report Body
Reports -> HeadInfo: Render Report Header
Reports --> User: Show Visualization History

== Multi-Process Handling (Backend) ==
note over ExpressServer: Cluster Module spawns\nmultiple worker processes
ExpressServer -> ExpressServer: Master Process Forks Workers
loop For Each Worker
    ExpressServer -> ExpressServer: Worker Binds to Port
    ExpressServer -> ExpressServer: Handle Requests
end

== Error Scenarios ==
Browser -> ExpressServer: Request (Any)
ExpressServer -> Authorize: Check Authorization
Authorize --> ExpressServer: Authorization Failed
ExpressServer --> Browser: 401 Unauthorized
Browser -> Router: Redirect to Login
Router --> User: Show Login Screen

ExpressServer -> Database: Database Query
Database --> ExpressServer: Connection Error\n(Too Many Connections)
ExpressServer --> Browser: 500 Internal Server Error
Browser --> User: Display Error Message

@enduml
